{"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"AppcuesKit"}],"title":"Configuring the Appcues URL Scheme","role":"article"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/appcueskit\/urlschemeconfiguring"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/URLSchemeConfiguring","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Appcues iOS SDK includes support for a custom URL scheme that supports previewing Appcues experiences in-app prior to publishing and launching the Appcues debugger."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuring the Appcues URL scheme involves adding a "},{"code":"CFBundleURLTypes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value and then directing the incoming URL to the Appcues iOS SDK."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"strongly","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" recommended that you configure the custom URL scheme. It allows non-developer users of your Appcues instance to test Appcues experiences in a real setting. It’s also valuable for future troubleshooting and support from Appcues via the debugger."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"text":"Register the Custom URL Scheme","anchor":"Register-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Info.plist"},{"type":"text","text":" to register the custom URL scheme. Replace "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID"},{"type":"text","text":" in the snippet below with your app’s Appcues Application ID. This value can be obtained from your "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/studio.appcues.com\/settings\/installation"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if your Appcues Application ID is "},{"code":"123-xyz","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" your url scheme value would be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appcues-123-xyz"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["<key>CFBundleURLTypes<\/key>","<array>","    <dict>","        <key>CFBundleTypeRole<\/key>","        <string>Editor<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLName<\/key>","        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLSchemes<\/key>","        <array>","            <string>appcues-APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID<\/string>","        <\/array>","    <\/dict>","<\/array>"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Handle the Custom URL Scheme","level":2,"anchor":"Handle-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom URL’s should be handled with a call to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/filterAndHandle(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/didHandleURL(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":". If the URL being opened is an Appcues URL, the URL will be handled.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app uses a Scene delegate, add the following:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func scene(_ scene: UIScene, willConnectTo session: UISceneSession, options connectionOptions: UIScene.ConnectionOptions) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(connectionOptions.urlContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}","","func scene(_ scene: UIScene, openURLContexts URLContexts: Set<UIOpenURLContext>) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(URLContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses only an App delegate, add the following:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func application(_ application: UIApplication, open url: URL, options: [UIApplication.OpenURLOptionsKey : Any] = [:] ) -> Bool {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return true }","","    \/\/ Handle a non-Appcues URL.","    return false","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A SwiftUI app can handle the custom URL scheme as part of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onOpenURL"},{"text":" modifier associated with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Scene","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of your main "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"App"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","        MyApp()","        .onOpenURL { url in","            guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Verifying-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Verifying the Custom URL Scheme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Appcues debugger allows you to easily validate that the Appcues deep link is properly configured.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Launch the debugger in your app with a call to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/debug()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Expand the debugger by tapping the floating button.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Tap the “Appcues Deep Link Configured” row to verify the status. If a checkmark appears, the Appcues deep link is properly configured.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"Troubleshooting","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Troubleshooting"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Error 0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": The Appcues debugger was unable to set up the verification test.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error 1"},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFBundleURLSchemes"},{"text":" value is missing. Refer to the “Register the Custom URL Scheme” section above.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Error 2","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": The URL scheme is registered, but the Appcues SDK did not receive the link from the host app. Refer to the “Handle the Custom URL Scheme” section above.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error 3"},{"type":"text","text":": The Appcues SDK received the link, but the verification token value was unexpected. Testing again should resolve the issue."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Debugging","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for details on the functionality of the debugger.","type":"text"}]}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Core Functionality","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Identifying","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Tracking","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/AnchoredTooltips","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation